d television have shaped not only how the general public sees trans people, but also how trans people see themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aTransgender people in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2019z9783110605785oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065352640uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081359737940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813597379423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813597379.jpg  a978-3-11-061001-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065352-6  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPKb2019